obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (20890)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20890&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Food Corporations Act,`
  line 1964.
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date ^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 67 of 1972, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15-12-1972).`
  line
  line `2 17th December, 1964, vide notification No. G.S.R. 1808, dated 16th December, 1964, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3 (i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (20891)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. Act 67 of 1972, s. 3 (w.e.f. 15-12-1972).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20891&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Corporation" means the Food Corporation of India established under section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "Food Corporation" means the Food Corporation of India established under section 3 or a`
  line `State Food Corporation established under section 17;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(bb) "foodstuffs" includes edible oilseeds and oils;]`
  line
  line `(c) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) "scheduled bank" means a bank for the time being included in the Second Schedule to the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(e) "State Food Corporation" means a State Food Corporation established under section 17;`
  line
  line `(f) "year" means the financial year.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (20892)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of Food Corporation of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20892&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf, the Central Government`
  line `shall establish for the purposes of this Act a Corporation known as the Food Corporation of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation shall be a body corporate with the name aforesaid having perpetual succession`
  line `and a common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of`
  line `property and to contract, and may, by that name, sue and be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (20893)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Offices and agencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 15-12-1972).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20893&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The head office of the Corporation shall be at Madras or at such other`
  line `place as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.`
  line
  line [^1
  line `(2) The Corporation may establish offices or agencies at other places in or outside India:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such office or agency shall be established at any place outside India without the`
  line `previous approval of the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (20894)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Capital of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20894&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The original capital of the Corporation shall be such sum not`
  line `exceeding one hundred crores of rupees as the Central Government may fix.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may from time to time increase the capital of the Corporation to such`
  line `extent and in such manner as that Government may determine.`
  line
  line `(3) Such capital may be provided by the Central Government from time to time after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law for the purpose and subject to such terms and conditions as may`
  line `be determined by that Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (20895)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Management.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20895&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general superintendence, direction and management of the affairs and`
  line `business of the Corporation shall vest in a board of directors which may exercise all such powers and do`
  line `all such acts and things as may be exercised or done by the Corporation under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The board of directors, in discharging its functions, shall act on business principles having regard`
  line `to the interests of the producer and consumer and shall be guided by such instructions on questions of`
  line `policy as may be given to it by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) If any doubt arises as to whether a question is or is not a question of policy, the decision of the`
  line `Central Government thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (20896)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Board of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20896&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The board of directors of the Corporation shall consist of the following,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman;`
  line
  line `(b) three directors to represent respectively the Ministries of the Central Government dealing`
  line with--
  line
  line `(i) food,`
  line
  line `(ii) finance, and`
  line
  line `(iii) co-operation;`
  line
  line `(c) the managing director of the Central Warehousing Corporation established under section 3 of`
  line `the Warehousing Corporations Act, 1962 (8 of 1962), ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) a managing director;`
  line
  line `(e) six other directors.`
  line
  line `(2) All the directors of the Corporation other than the director referred to in clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be appointed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The managing director, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) exercise such powers and perform such duties as the board of directors may entrust or`
  line `delegate to him; and`
  line
  line `(b) receive such salary and allowances as the board of directors may, with the approval of the`
  line `Central Government, fix:`
  line
  line `Provided that the first managing director shall receive such salary and allowances as the Central`
  line `Government may fix.`
  line
  line `(4) The term of office of, and the manner of filling casual vacancies among, the directors of the`
  line `Corporation, other than the director referred to in clause (c) of sub-section (1), and the other terms and`
  line `conditions of appointment of the directors of the Corporation shall, subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (3), be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (20897)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Disqualification for office of director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20897&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `A person shall be disqualified for being appointed as,`
  line `and for being, a director of the Corporation--`
  line
  line `(a) if he is, or at any time has been, adjudicated insolvent or has suspended payment of his debts`
  line `or has compounded with his creditors; or`
  line
  line `(b) if he is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(c) if he is or has been convicted of any offence which in the opinion of the Central Government`
  line `involves moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(d) if he has been removed or dismissed from the service of the Government or a corporation`
  line `owned or controlled by the Government; or`
  line
  line `(e) except in the case of the Chairman or the managing director, if he is a salaried official of the`
  line `Food Corporation of India or a State Food Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (20898)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Removal and resignation of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20898&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, at any time, after`
  line `consultation with the Corporation, remove the managing director from office after giving him a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the proposed removal.`
  line
  line `(2) The board of directors may remove any director from office who--`
  line
  line `(a) is or has become subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in section 8; or`
  line
  line `(b) is absent without leave of the board of directors from more than three consecutive meetings`
  line `thereof without cause sufficient, in the opinion of the board, to exonerate his absence.`
  line
  line `(3) A director of the Corporation may resign his office by giving notice thereof in writing to the`
  line `Central Government and on such resignation being accepted, he shall be deemed to have vacated his`
  line office.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (20899)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Meetings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20899&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The board of directors of the Corporation shall meet at such times and places and`
  line `shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the`
  line `quorum at meetings) as may be provided by regulations made by the Corporation under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman of the Board or, if for any reason he is unable to attend any meeting, any other`
  line `director elected by the directors present at the meeting, shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) All questions which come up before any meeting of the board shall be decided by a majority of`
  line `the votes of the directors present and voting, and, in the event of an equality of votes, the Chairman, or in`
  line `his absence, the person presiding, shall have and exercise a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (20900)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Advisory Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20900&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, in consultation with the Corporation,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute one or more Advisory Committees consisting of such`
  line `persons and on such terms and conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of any such Advisory Committee to advice the Central Government or the`
  line `Corporation in regard to any matter connected with the purposes of this Act in respect of which its advice`
  line `is sought by the Central Government, or, as the case may be, by the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(3) The expenses in relation to the Advisory Committees shall be met by the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (20901)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Officers and other employees of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20901&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall after`
  line `consultation with the Corporation, appoint a person to be the Secretary of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to such rules as may be made by the Central Government in this behalf, the Corporation`
  line `may appoint such other officers and employees as it considers necessary for the efficient performance of`
  line `its functions.`
  line
  line `(3) The methods of appointment, the conditions of service and the scales of pay of the officers and`
  line `other employees of the Corporation shall--`
  line
  line `(a) as respects the Secretary, be such as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) as respects the other officers and employees, be such as may be determined by regulations`
  line `made by the Corporation under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (20902)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 13
  title `Special provisions for transfer of Government employees to the Corporation in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20902&sectionno=12A&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Special provisions for transfer of Government employees to the Corporation in certain`
  line `cases.--(1) Where the Central Government has ceased or ceases to perform any functions which under`
  line `section 13 are functions of the Corporation, it shall be lawful for the Central Government to transfer, by`
  line `order and with effect from such date or dates (which may be either retrospective to any date not earlier`
  line `than the 1st January, 1965, or prospective) as may be specified in the order, to the Corporation any of the`
  line `officers or employees serving in the Department of the Central Government dealing with food or any of`
  line `its subordinate or attached offices and engaged in the performance of those functions:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order under this sub-section shall be made in relation to any officer or employee in`
  line `such Department or office who has, in respect of the proposal of the Central Government to transfer such`
  line `officer or employee to the Corporation, intimated within such time as may be specified in this behalf by`
  line `that Government, his intention of not becoming an employee of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) In making an order under sub-section (1), the Central Government shall, as far as may be, take`
  line `into consideration the functions which the Central Government has ceased or ceases to perform and the`
  line `areas in which such functions have been or are performed.`
  line
  line `(3) An officer or other employee transferred by an order made under sub-section (1) shall, on and`
  line `from the date of transfer, cease to be an employee of the Central Government and become an employee of`
  line `the Corporation with such designation as the Corporation may determine and shall, ^2[subject to the`
  line `provisions of sub-sections (4), (4A), (4B), (4C), (5) and (6)], be governed by the regulations made by the`
  line `Corporation under this Act as respects remuneration and other conditions of service including pension,`
  line `leave and provident fund, and shall continue to be an officer or employee of the Corporation unless and`
  line `until his employment is terminated by the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(4) Every officer or other employee transferred by an order made under sub-section (1) shall, within`
  line `six months from the date of transfer, exercise his option in writing to be governed,--`
  line
  line `(a) by the scale of pay applicable to the post held by him under the Government immediately`
  line `before the date of transfer or by the scale of pay applicable to the post under the Corporation to which`
  line `he is transferred,`
  line
  line `(b) by the leave, provident fund, retirement or other terminal benefits admissible to employees of`
  line `the Central Government in accordance with the rules and others of the Central Government as`
  line `amended from time to time or the leave, provident fund or other terminal benefits admissible to the`
  line `employees of the Corporation under the regulations made by the Corporation under this Act,`
  line
  line `and such option once exercised shall be final:`
  line
  line `Provided that the option exercised under clause (a) shall be applicable only in respect of the post to`
  line `which such officer or employee is transferred to the Corporation and on appointment to a higher post`
  line `under the Corporation, he shall be eligible only for the scale of pay applicable to such higher post:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if immediately before the date of his transfer any such officer or employee is`
  line `officiating in a higher post under the Government either in a leave vacancy or in any other vacancy of a`
  line `specified duration, his pay, on transfer, shall be protected for the unexpired period of such vacancy and`
  line `thereafter he shall be entitled to the scale of pay applicable to the post under the Government to which he`
  line `would have reverted or to the scale of pay applicable to the post under the Corporation to which he is`
  line `transferred, whichever he may opt:`
  line
  line `Provided also that when an officer or other employee serving in the Department of the Ministry of the`
  line `Central Government dealing with food or in any of its attached or subordinate offices is promoted to`
  line `officiate in a higher post in the Department or office subsequent to the transfer to the Corporation of any`
  line `other officer or employee senior to him in that Department or office before such transfer, the officer or`
  line `other employee who is promoted to officiate in such higher post shall, on transfer to the Corporation, be entitled only to the scale of pay applicable to the post he would have held but for such promotion or the`
  line `scale of pay applicable to the post under the Corporation to which he is transferred, whichever he may`
  line opt.
  line
  line `^3[(4A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (4),--`
  line
  line `(a) every officer or other employee in respect of whom an order of transfer under sub-section (1)`
  line `had been made before the date of commencement of the Food Corporations (Amendment) Act, 1977`
  line `(hereafter in this section referred to as the appointed day) shall, whether or not he had exercised the`
  line `option under sub-section (4) before the appointed day, exercise such option within six months from`
  line `the appointed day; and`
  line
  line `(b) every officer or other employee in respect of whom an order of transfer under sub-section (1)`
  line `may be made after the appointed day shall, within six months from the date of such order, exercise his`
  line `option under sub-section (4),`
  line
  line `and in each such case such option once exercised shall be final:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an officer or other employee having exercised an option under sub-section (4)`
  line `before the appointed day,--`
  line
  line `(i) has died or retired before the appointed day, or dies or retires after the appointed day,`
  line `before exercising the option as required by this sub-section, or`
  line
  line `(ii) does not exercise the option as required by this sub-section,`
  line
  line `the option already exercised by him shall be deemed to have been validly exercised by him under`
  line `sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(4B) Where an officer or other employee--`
  line
  line `(a) has died or retired, or dies or retires, after an order of transfer under sub-section (1) in respect`
  line `of such officer or other employee is made but before exercising the option under sub-section (4) or, as`
  line `the case may be, as required by sub-section (4A); or`
  line
  line `(b) has died or retired, or dies or retires, before an order of transfer under sub-section (1) in`
  line `respect of such officer or other employee is made,`
  line
  line `he shall, notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (4) or sub-section (4A),--`
  line
  line `(i) in a case falling under clause (a), be deemed to have exercised an option under sub-section (4);`
  line and
  line
  line `(ii) in a case falling under clause (b), be deemed to have been transferred under sub-section (1)`
  line `and exercised an option under sub-section (4),`
  line
  line `to be governed by the leave, provident fund, retirement or other terminal benefits admissible to the`
  line `employees of the Central Government in accordance with the rules and orders of the Central Government`
  line `as amended from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in clause (a) of this sub-section shall apply to an officer or other employee who`
  line `has, before the appointed day been paid the terminal benefits as admissible to the employees of the`
  line `Corporation under the regulations made by the Corporation under this Act, unless such officer or other`
  line `employee refunds in a lump sum within six months from the appointed day the amount of contributions`
  line `made by the Corporation towards such terminal benefits:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in clause (b) of this sub-section shall apply to an officer or other`
  line `employee who has intimated, under the proviso to sub-section (1), his intention of not becoming an`
  line `employee of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(4C) Where an officer or other employee has exercised an option under sub-section (4), or exercises,`
  line `or is deemed to have exercised, an option under that sub-section, read with sub-section (4A) or`
  line `sub-section (4B), to be governed by the leave, provident fund, retirement or other terminal benefits`
  line `admissible to the employees of the Central Government, such benefits shall be calculated on the basis of`
  line `the pay and allowances drawn by him in the Corporation.]`
  line
  line `(5) No officer or other employee transferred by an order made under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) shall be dismissed or removed by an authority subordinate to that competent to make a similar`
  line `or equivalent appointment under the Corporation as may be specified in the regulations made by the`
  line `Corporation under this Act;`
  line
  line `^4[(b) shall be dismissed or removed or reduced in rank except after an inquiry in which he has`
  line `been informed of the charges against him and given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in`
  line `respect of those charges:]`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that where it is proposed after such inquiry, to impose upon him any such penalty, such`
  line `penalty may be imposed on the basis of the evidence adduced during such inquiry and it shall not be`
  line `necessary to give such person any opportunity of making representation on the penalty proposed:]`
  line
  line `^6[Provided further that] this clause shall not apply,--`
  line
  line `(i) where an officer or employee is dismissed or removed or reduced in rank on the ground of`
  line `conduct which has led to his conviction on a criminal charge; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where the authority empowered to dismiss or remove an officer or employee or to reduce him`
  line `in rank is satisfied that for some reason, to be recorded by that authority in writing, it is not`
  line `reasonably practicable to hold such inquiry; or`
  line
  line `(iii) to an officer or employee who, after transfer to the Corporation, is appointed to a higher post`
  line `under the Corporation in response to an open advertisement and in competition with outsiders.`
  line
  line `(6) If, in respect of any such officer or employee as aforesaid, a question arises whether it is`
  line `reasonably practicable to hold such inquiry as is referred to in sub-section (5), the decision thereon of the`
  line `authority empowered to dismiss or remove him or to reduce him in rank shall be final.`
  line
  line `(7) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall apply to the members of the Central Secretariat Service`
  line `or any other service or to persons on deputation to the Department referred to in that sub-section or to any`
  line `of its attached or subordinate offices from any Ministry of the Central Government or from any State`
  line `Government or from any organisation.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 57 of 1968, s. 2 (w.e.f 28-12-1968).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 1977, s. 2, for "subject to the provisions of sub-sections (4), (5) and (6)" (w.e.f. 31-12-1976).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 12 of 1977, s. 2 (w.e.f. 31-12-1976).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 53 of 1982, s. 2, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 21-10-1982).`
  line
  line `5. The proviso ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-10-1982).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Provided that" (w.e.f. 21-10-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (20903)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Functions of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20903&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, it shall be the primary duty`
  line `of the Corporation to undertake the purchase, storage, movement, transport, distribution and sale of`
  line `foodgrains and other foodstuffs.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject as aforesaid, the Corporation may also, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line Government,--
  line
  line `(a) promote by such means as it thinks fit the production of foodgrains and other foodstuffs;`
  line
  line `(b) set up, or assist in the setting up of, rice mills, flour mills and other undertakings for the`
  line `processing of foodgrains and other foodstuffs, and`
  line
  line `(c) discharge such other functions as may be prescribed or as are supplemental, incidental or`
  line `consequential to any of the functions conferred on it under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (20904)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Executive Committee and other commodities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20904&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The board of directors of the Corporation`
  line `may constitute an Executive Committee which shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairman of the board;`
  line
  line `(b) the managing director; and`
  line
  line `(c) three other directors, of whom one shall be a non-official.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman of the board of directors shall be the Chairman of the Executive Committee.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the general control, direction and superintendence of the board of directors, the`
  line `Executive Committee shall be competent to deal with any matter within the competence of the`
  line Corporation.
  line
  line `(4) The board of directors may constitute such other committees, whether consisting wholly of`
  line `directors or wholly of other persons or partly of directors and partly of other persons as it thinks fit, for`
  line `such purposes as it may decide.`
  line
  line `(5) A committee constituted under this section shall meet at such times and places and shall observe`
  line `such rules of procedure in reward to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at`
  line `meetings) as may be provided by regulations made by the Corporation under this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) The members of a committee (other than the directors of the board) shall be paid by the`
  line `Corporation such fees and allowances as may be fixed by it by regulations made under this Act for`
  line `attending the meetings of the committee and for attending to any other work of the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (20905)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Member of board or committee thereof not to vote in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20905&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `A member of the board`
  line `of directors of the Corporation or a committee thereof who has any direct or indirect pecuniary interest in`
  line `any matter coming up for consideration at a meeting of the board of directors or committee thereof, shall,`
  line `as soon as possible after relevant circumstances have come to his knowledge, disclose the nature of his`
  line `interest at such meeting and the disclosure shall be recorded in the minutes of the board or the committee,`
  line `as the case may be, and the member shall not take any part in any deliberation or decision of the board or`
  line `committee with respect to that matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (20906)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Boards of Management, their constitution and functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20906&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may,`
  line `on a request received in this behalf from the State Government or Governments concerned or otherwise,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, establish a Board of Management for a State or two or more`
  line `contiguous States, if no State Food Corporation is functioning in such State or States.`
  line
  line `(2) The head office of the Board of Management shall be at such place as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board of Management shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman to be appointed by the Board of directors of the Food Corporation of India;`
  line
  line `(b) the senior-most executive officer of the said Corporation employed at the head office of the`
  line `Board of Management; and`
  line
  line `(c) not more than ten other members to be appointed by the Board of directors of the said`
  line Corporation.
  line
  line `(4) The members of a Board of Management referred to in clauses (a) and (c) of sub-section (3) shall`
  line `hold office for a term of two years and shall be eligible for re-appointment and the other terms and`
  line `conditions of their appointment shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board of Management shall advise the Corporation on such matters as may be generally or`
  line `specifically referred to it and shall perform such other functions as the Corporation may delegate to it.`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of sections 20, 21 and 25 shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to the members`
  line `of a Board of Management as they apply in relation to the members of the Board of directors of a State`
  line `Food Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided that the reference to the General Manager in clause (e) of section 20 shall be construed as a`
  line `reference to the officer of the Corporation referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(7) The Food Corporation of India may, after consultation with a Board of Management, appoint such`
  line `staff as it considers necessary to enable that Board to perform its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(8) The Board of Management may, by order in writing, authorise any one or more of its members to`
  line `exercise and perform, subject to such conditions and limitations, if any, as may be specified in the order,`
  line `such of its powers and functions as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(9) The Board of Management shall follow such procedure as may be provided by regulations made`
  line `by the Food Corporation of India under this Act.`
  line
  line `(10) Where a Board of Management has been established--`
  line
  line `(i) for a State, or`
  line
  line `(ii) for two or more States,`
  line
  line `then such Board shall stand dissolved-`
  line
  line `(a) in the case referred to in clause (i), on the establishment of a Food Corporation for that State,`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) in the case referred to in clause (ii), on the establishment of such Corporation for any one or`
  line `more of such States.`
  line
  line `(11) Where a Board of Management stands dissolved under clause (b) of sub-section (10), the Central`
  line `Government may establish a new Board of Management for the State or States for which no Food`
  line `Corporation has been established.`
  line
  line `(12) The expenses of the Board of Management in the discharge of its functions under this Act shall`
  line `be met by the Food Corporation of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (20907)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Establishment of State Food Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20907&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette and after consultation with the Government of a State, establish a Food`
  line `Corporation for that State under such name as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) A State Food Corporation established under sub-section (1) shall be a body corporate by the name`
  line `notified under that sub-section, having perpetual succession and a common seal with power, subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property and to contract, and may, by the said`
  line `name, sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of a State Food Corporation shall be at such place within the State as may be`
  line `notified by the Central Government in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of this Act, a State Food Corporation may perform such of the functions`
  line `of the Food Corporation of India as that Corporation may delegate to it.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (20908)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Capital of State Food Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20908&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Capital of a State Food Corporation shall be such`
  line `sum not exceeding ten crores of rupees as the Central Government may, after consultation with the Food`
  line `Corporation of India, fix.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, after such consultation, from time to time, increase the capital of`
  line `the State Food Corporation to such extent and in such manner as that Government may determine.`
  line
  line `(3) Such capital shall be provided--`
  line
  line `(a) by the Central Government after due appropriation made by Parliament by law for the`
  line `purpose, and`
  line
  line `(b) by the Food Corporation of India,`
  line
  line `in such proportion and subject to such terms and conditions as may be determined by the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (20909)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Management of State Food Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20909&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general superintendence, direction and`
  line `management of the affairs and business of a State Food Corporation shall vest in a board of directors`
  line `which shall consist of a Chairman, a General Manager and not more than ten other members, all of whom`
  line `shall be appointed by the Food Corporation of India after consultation with the Central Government and`
  line `the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The General Manager shall--`
  line
  line `(a) exercise such powers and perform such duties as the board of directors may entrust or`
  line `delegate to him; and`
  line
  line `(b) receive such salary and allowances and be governed by such terms and conditions of service`
  line `as the board of directors may, in consultation with the Food Corporation of India, fix.`
  line
  line `(3) The board of directors, in discharging its functions, shall act on business principles having regard`
  line `to the interests of the producer and consumer and shall be guided by such instructions on questions of`
  line `policy as may be given to it by the Food Corporation of India.`
  line
  line `(4) If any doubt arises as to whether a question is or is not a question of policy, the matter shall be`
  line `referred to the Central Government whose decision thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(5) The members of the board of directors, other than the General Manager, shall be entitled to`
  line `receive by way of remuneration or fees such sums as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no official member shall be entitled to receive any remuneration other than any`
  line `allowances admissible to him under the rules regulating his conditions of service.`
  line
  line `(6) The term of office of, and the manner of filling casual vacancies among, the members of the board`
  line `of directors shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (20910)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Disqualification for office of member of board of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20910&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `A person shall be disqualified`
  line `for being appointed as, and for being, a member of the board of directors of a State Food Corporation--`
  line
  line `(a) if he is, or at any time has been adjudicated insolvent or has suspended payment of his debts`
  line `or has compounded with his creditors; or`
  line
  line `(b) if he is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(c) if he is or has been convicted of any offence which in the opinion of the Central Government`
  line `involves moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(d) if he has been removed or dismissed from the service of the Government or a corporation`
  line `owned or controlled by the Government; or`
  line
  line `(e) except in the case of the Chairman or the General Manager, if he is a salaried official of the`
  line `Food Corporation of India or a State Food Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (20911)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Removal and resignation of members of board of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20911&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Food Corporation of`
  line `India may, at any time, after consultation with the State Food Corporation, remove the General Manager`
  line `from office after giving him a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the proposed removal.`
  line
  line `(2) The board of directors of a State Food Corporation may remove from office any member of that`
  line `board who--`
  line
  line `(a) is or has become subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in section 20; or`
  line
  line `(b) is absent without leave of the board of directors from more than three consecutive meetings`
  line `thereof without cause sufficient, in the opinion of the board, to exonerate his absence.`
  line
  line `(3) A member of such board may resign his office by giving notice thereof in writing to the Food`
  line `Corporation of India and on such resignation being accepted, he shall be deemed to have vacated his`
  line office.
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (20912)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title Meetings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20912&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The board of directors of a State Food Corporation shall meet at such times and`
  line `places and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at meetings) as may be provided by regulations made by that Corporation under`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman of the board of directors, or, if for any reason he is unable to attend any meeting,`
  line `any other member of the board elected by the members of the board present at the meeting, shall preside`
  line `at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) All questions which come up before any meeting of the board of directors shall be decided by a`
  line `majority of the votes of the members present and voting, and in the event of an equality of votes, the`
  line `Chairman or in his absence, the person presiding shall have and exercise a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (20913)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Appointment of officers, etc. and their conditions of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20913&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) A State Food Corporation`
  line `may appoint such officers and other employees as it considers necessary for the efficient performance of`
  line `its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person employed by a State Food Corporation under this Act shall be subject to such`
  line `conditions of service and shall be entitled to such remuneration as may be determined by regulations`
  line `made by the Corporation under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (20914)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Executive Committee and other committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20914&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The board of directors of a State Food`
  line `corporation may constitute an Executive Committee which shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairman of the board of directors;`
  line
  line `(b) the General Manager; and`
  line
  line `(c) three other members of the board of directors, of whom one shall be a non-official.`
  line
  line `(2) the Chairman of the board of directors shall be the Chairman of the Executive Committee.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the general control, direction and superintendence of the board of directors, the`
  line `Executive Committee shall be competent to deal with any matter within the competence of the State Food`
  line Corporation.
  line
  line `(4) The board of directors may constitute such other committees, whether consisting wholly of`
  line `members of the board or wholly of other persons or partly of such members and partly of other persons as`
  line `it thinks fit, for such purposes as it may decide.`
  line
  line `(5) A committee constituted under this section shall meet at such times and places and shall observe`
  line `such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at`
  line `meetings) as may be provided by regulations made by the State Food Corporation under this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) The members of a committee (other than the directors of the board) shall be paid by the State`
  line `Food Corporation such fees and allowances as may be fixed by it by regulations made under this Act, for`
  line `attending the meetings of the committee and for attending to any other work of that Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (20915)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Member of board or committee thereof not to vote in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20915&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `A member of the board`
  line `of directors of a State Food Corporation or a committee thereof who has any direct or indirect pecuniary`
  line `interest in any matter coming up for consideration at a meeting of the board of directors or committee`
  line `thereof, shall, as soon as possible after relevant circumstances have come to his knowledge, disclose the`
  line `nature of his interest at such meeting and the disclosure shall be recorded in the minutes of the board or`
  line `the committee, as the case may be, and the member shall not take any part in any deliberation or decision`
  line `of the board or the committee with respect to that matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (20916)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Submission of programme of activities and financial estimates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20916&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Food Corporation`
  line `shall, before the commencement of each year, prepare a statement of programme of its activities during`
  line `the forthcoming year as well as a financial estimate in respect thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) The statement prepared under sub-section (1) shall not less than three months before the`
  line `commencement of each year, be submitted for approval--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the Food Corporation of India, to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a State Food Corporation, to the Food Corporation of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The statement and the financial estimate of a Food Corporation referred to in sub-section (1) may,`
  line `with the approval of the Central Government, in the case of the Food Corporation of India, or with the`
  line `approval of the Food Corporation of India in the case of a State Food Corporation, be revised by the Food`
  line Corporation.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (20917)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Borrowing powers of Food Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20917&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `^10[(1) A Food Corporation may, for the purpose of`
  line `carrying out its functions under this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) take advances against stocks of foodgrains or other foodstuffs held by it, or borrow money--`
  line
  line `(i) from any scheduled bank, or`
  line
  line `(ii) from any other bank or financial institution approved by the Central Government in this`
  line `behalf, or`
  line
  line `(iii) from any other authority, organisation or institution or from the public on such terms and`
  line `conditions as may be approved by the Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) issue and sell bonds and debentures carrying interest at such rates as may be fixed by the`
  line `Central Government at the time the bonds or debentures are issued:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the amount borrowed by a Food Corporation under clause (b) shall not at any time`
  line `exceed ten times the paid-up capital and the reserve fund established under section 33.]]`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may guarantee the loans and advances taken by a Food Corporation`
  line `under sub-section (1) as to the re-payment of principal and the payment of interest thereon and other`
  line `incidental charges.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) A Food Corporation may, for the purpose of carrying out its functions under this Act, also`
  line `borrow money from the Central Government; and that Government may, after due appropriation made by`
  line `Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Food Corporation such sums of money by way of loan on`
  line `such terms and conditions as that Government may determine.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 1988, s. 2, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 20-8-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2001, s. 2, for the proviso (w.e.f. 22-5-2001).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 67 of 1972, s. 5 (w.e.f. 15-12-1972).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (20918)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Lending by Food Corporation on security of foodgrains.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20918&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `A Food Corporation may lend or`
  line `advance money to any person engaged in the production of foodgrains upon the security of foodgrains or`
  line `such other security as may be prescribed, for any purpose connected with such production.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (20919)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to enter into agreement for purchase of foodgrains after harvest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20919&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Food`
  line `Corporation may enter into agreement with any grower of foodcrops for the purchase of foodgrains after`
  line `the harvest of such crops and any such agreement may provide that any sum payable by the Corporation`
  line `to the grower under such agreement shall be payable to any scheduled bank or other financing agency`
  line `nominated by the grower in this behalf to such extent as may be specified in the agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) The scheduled bank or other financing agency referred to in sub-section (1) may, on the basis of`
  line `any agreement referred to in that sub-section, lend money to a grower of food crops who has entered into`
  line `such agreement.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (20920)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Guarantee by Food Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20920&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `A Food Corporation may, upon such terms and conditions`
  line `as it may think fit, guarantee any loan referred to in sub-section (2) of section 29, and also any other loan`
  line `raised by a grower of foodcrops, which is re-payable within a period not exceeding five years.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (20921)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 32
  title `Funds of Food Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20921&sectionno=31&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Food Corporation shall have its own fund and all receipts`
  line `of the Corporation shall be credited thereto and all payments of the Corporation shall be met therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) Such fund shall be applied for meeting all administrative expenses of the Food Corporation and`
  line `for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (20922)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 33
  title `Investment of funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20922&sectionno=32&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `A Food Corporation may invest its funds in the securities of the Central`
  line `Government or any State Government or in such other manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (20923)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 34
  title `Allocation of surplus profits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20923&sectionno=33&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Food Corporation shall establish a reserve fund to which`
  line `shall be credited every year such portion of its annual net profits as that Corporation thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) After making provision for such reserve fund and for bad and doubtful debts, depreciation in`
  line `assets and all other matters which are usually provided for by companies registered and incorporated`
  line `under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), the balance of its annual net profits shall be paid--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the Food Corporation of India, to the Central Government, and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a State Food Corporation, to the Central Government and the Food Corporation`
  line `of India in the same proportion as the capital provided by them.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (20924)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 35
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 2000, s. 2, for section 34 (w.e.f. 2-6-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20924&sectionno=34&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `^1[34. Accounts and audit.--(1) A Food Corporation shall maintain proper accounts and other`
  line `relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts including the profit and loss account and the`
  line `balance-sheet in such form as may be prescribed by the Central Government in consultation with the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of a Food Corporation shall be audited annually by the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such audit shall be`
  line `payable by the Food Corporation to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of a Food Corporation shall have the same rights, privileges and authority`
  line `in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General has in connection with the audit of`
  line `Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of books, accounts,`
  line `connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any office of the Food Corporation.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of a Food Corporation as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `or any other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be`
  line `forwarded annually by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India to,--`
  line
  line `(i) the Food Corporation concerned;`
  line
  line `(ii) where the accounts relate to a State Food Corporation, also to the Food Corporation of India;`
  line
  line `(iii) the Central Government,`
  line
  line `and that Government shall, as soon thereafter as may be, cause the same to be laid before both Houses of`
  line Parliament.]
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (20925)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 36
  title `Annual report on the working of Food Corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 67 of 1972, s. 7 (w.e.f. 15-12-1972).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20925&sectionno=35&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Food Corporation shall, as soon`
  line `as possible after the end of each year, submit to the Central Government an annual report on the working`
  line `and affairs of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall, as soon as may be after the receipt of such report, cause such`
  line `report and the audit report received under section 34 ^1[together with any comments thereon or supplement`
  line `thereto by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India] to be laid before both Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (20926)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 37
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate acts or proceedings of Food Corporation, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20926&sectionno=36&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) No act or`
  line `proceeding of a Food Corporation or a committee thereof or a Board of Management shall be invalid by`
  line `reason only of the existence of any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the board of directors`
  line `of the Food Corporation or such Committee or Board of Management.`
  line
  line `(2) No act done by any person acting in good faith as a member of a board of directors of a Food`
  line `Corporation or of a Board of Management shall be deemed to be invalid by reason only of his`
  line `disqualification for being appointed as, or for being, a member of such board of directors or Board of`
  line Management.
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (20927)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 38
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20927&sectionno=37&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `A Food Corporation may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to the`
  line `Chairman or any other member of the board of directors or the Secretary or other officer of the`
  line `Corporation, subject to such conditions and limitations, if any, as may be specified in the order, such of`
  line `its powers and functions under this Act as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (20928)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 39
  title `Declaration of fidelity and secrecy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20928&sectionno=38&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `Every director, member of an Advisory Committee or`
  line `other committee, auditor, officer or other employee of a Food Corporation and every member of a Board`
  line `of Management and its staff shall, before entering upon his duties, make a declaration of fidelity and`
  line `secrecy in the form set out in the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (20929)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 40
  title `Indemnity of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20929&sectionno=39&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every member of the board of directors of a Food Corporation and`
  line `of a Board of Management shall be indemnified by the Corporation against all losses and expenses`
  line `incurred by him in the discharge of his duties except such as are caused by his own wilful act or default.`
  line
  line `(2) A member of the board of directors of a Food Corporation or a Board of Management shall not be`
  line `responsible for any other member or for any officer or other employee of the Corporation or Board of`
  line `Management or for any loss or expense resulting to the Corporation from the insufficiency or deficiency`
  line `of value of, or title to, any property or security acquired or taken on behalf of the Corporation in good`
  line `faith, or by the insolvency or wrongful act of any person under obligation to the Corporation or by`
  line `anything done in good faith, in the execution of the duties of his office or in relation thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (20930)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 41
  title `Protection of action taken under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20930&sectionno=40&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against a`
  line `Food Corporation or any member of the board of directors thereof or any officer or other employee`
  line `thereof or any member of a Board of Management or its staff or any other person authorised by a Food`
  line `Corporation or a Board of Management to discharge any functions under this Act for any loss or damage`
  line `caused or likely to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance`
  line `of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (20931)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 42
  title Offences.
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20931&sectionno=41&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, without the consent in writing of a Food Corporation, uses its name in`
  line `any prospectus or advertisement, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `six months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) No court shall take cognizance of any offence under sub-section (1) except on a complaint in`
  line `writing by an officer authorised in this behalf by the Food Corporation concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (20932)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 43
  title `Provision relating to income-tax, super-tax, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20932&sectionno=42&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of the Income-tax`
  line `Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), or any other enactment for the time being in force relating to income-tax,`
  line `super-tax or any other tax on income, profits or gains, a Food Corporation shall be deemed to be a`
  line `company within the meaning of the Income-tax Act, 1961, and shall be liable to tax accordingly on its`
  line `income, profits and gains.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (20933)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 44
  title `Winding up of Food Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20933&sectionno=43&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `No provision of law relating to the winding up of`
  line `companies or corporations shall apply to a Food Corporation and it shall not be placed in liquidation save`
  line `by order of the Central Government and in such manner as that Government may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (20934)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 45
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 53 of 1982, s. 3, for certain words (w.e.f. 21-10-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20934&sectionno=44&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rule may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the term of office of, and the manner of filling casual vacancies among, and the other terms`
  line `and conditions of appointment of, the directors of the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(b) the composition of Advisory Committees and the terms and conditions of service of members`
  line thereof;
  line
  line `(c) the additional functions which the Corporation may perform;`
  line
  line `(d) the remuneration or fees payable to the members of the board of directors of a State Food`
  line `Corporation and the term of office of, and the manner of filling casual vacancies among, such`
  line members;
  line
  line `(e) the securities (other than food grains) upon which a Food Corporation may lend or advance`
  line money;
  line
  line `(f) the manner in which a Food Corporation may invest its funds;`
  line
  line `(g) the form of the annual statement of accounts and the balance sheet to be prepared by a Food`
  line Corporation;
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which has to be or may by prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this section shall be laid as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days`
  line `^1[which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry`
  line `of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid,] both Houses agree`
  line `in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule`
  line `shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so however`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously`
  line `done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (20935)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 46
  title `Power of Food Corporation to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20935&sectionno=45&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Food Corporation may, with the`
  line `previous sanction of the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations not`
  line `inconsistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder, to provide for all matters for which provision is`
  line `necessary or expedient for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `^1 [(1A) The power to make regulations under this section shall include the power to give retrospective`
  line `effect from a date not earlier than the date of commencement of this Act, to the regulations or any of them`
  line `but no retrospective effect shall be given to any regulation so as to prejudicially affect the interests of any`
  line `person to whom such regulation may be applicable.]`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulation may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the methods of appointment, the conditions of service and the scales of pay of the officers and`
  line `employees of a Food Corporation, other than the Secretary of the Food Corporation of India;`
  line
  line `(b) the duties and conduct of officers and employees of a Food Corporation, other than the`
  line `Secretary aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(c) the functions and duties which may be entrusted or delegated to the managing director or, as`
  line `the case may be, the General Manager, or a Food Corporation:`
  line
  line `(d) the times and places at which meetings of a Food Corporation or any committee thereof shall`
  line `be held and the procedure to be followed thereat;`
  line
  line `(e) the fees and allowances payable to the members of a committee under sub-section (6) of`
  line `section 14 or sub-section (6) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(f) generally, the efficient conduct of the affairs of a Food Corporation.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, rescind any regulation`
  line `which it has sanctioned and thereupon such regulation shall cease to have effect.`
  line
  line `(4) Any regulation which may be made by the Food Corporation of India under this Act may be made`
  line `by the Central Government within three months from the establishment of that Corporation and any`
  line `regulation which may be made by a State Food Corporation under this Act may be made by the Food`
  line `Corporation of India within three months from the establishment of such State Food Corporation; and any`
  line `regulation so made may be altered or rescinded by the Food Corporation concerned in the exercise of its`
  line `powers under this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[(5) Every regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that regulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Added by Act 53 of 1982, s. 4 (w.e.f 21-10-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (20936)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 47
  title Validation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f 21-10-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282&sectionId=20936&sectionno=46&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_196437_1517807322282
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `^1[46. Validation.--No regulation made or purporting to have been made with retrospective`
  line `effect, under section 45 before the commencement of the Food Corporations (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1982 (53 of 1982) shall be deemed to be invalid or ever to have been invalid merely on the ground`
  line `that such regulation was made with retrospective effect and accordingly every such regulation and any`
  line `action taken or thing done thereunder shall be as valid and effective as if the provisions of section 45, as`
  line `amended by the Food Corporations (Amendment) Act, 1982 were in force at all material times when such`
  line `regulation was made or action or thing was taken or done.]`
